article.headline: Pierce, Martini lead Princeton past Pennsylvania 105-83 to win Ivy League
article.description: — Caden Pierce scored 32 points, Zach Martini made seven 3-pointers and Princeton beat Pennsylvania 105-83 on Saturday night to claim the outright regular-season championship in the Ivy League.

article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- — Caden Pierce scored 32 points, Zach Martini made seven 3-pointers and Princeton beat Pennsylvania 105-83 on Saturday night to claim the outright regular-season championship in the Ivy League. Pierce also added nine rebounds for the Tigers (24-3, 12-2 Ivy League). Martini scored 23 points, going 8 of 10 overall and 7 for 9 from 3-point range. Xaivian Lee shot 5 of 9 from the field and 1 of 3 from the free-throw line to finish with 13 points. The Tigers stretched their winning streak to nine games. The Quakers (11-18, 3-11) were led by Clark Slajchert, who recorded 20 points and six assists. Pennsylvania also got 17 points and six rebounds from Nick Spinoso. Tyler Perkins also put up 17 points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
